│ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                             │
│ The user wants me to fix a crash in the LLVM `coro-split` pass when processing mutually recursive coroutines.                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The crash is an assertion failure: `!UR.InvalidatedSCCs.count(C) && "Invalidated the current SCC!"`. This happens in `updateCGAndAnalysisManagerForPass` which is   │
│ part of the CGSCC pass manager infrastructure. It indicates that a pass running on an SCC has invalidated that same SCC, which is not allowed.                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The backtrace shows the `CoroSplitPass` is running. The reproducer involves a coroutine `foo` and a function `bar` that call each other, forming a strongly         │
│ connected component (SCC) in the call graph.                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ `CoroSplitPass` transforms a coroutine function (`foo` in this case) into multiple functions (a ramp function, resume functions, etc.). This transformation         │
│ involves:                                                                                                                                                           │
│ 1.  Creating new functions.                                                                                                                                         │
│ 2.  Modifying the original function (`foo`) to become the ramp function.                                                                                            │
│ 3.  Changing call sites. For example, calls to the original coroutine `foo` (from `bar`) will be redirected to the new ramp function. Calls made from within the    │
│ coroutine `foo` (to `bar`) will be moved into the new resume functions.                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The process of updating the call graph after this transformation is complex. The `CoroSplitPass` calls `updateCallGraphAfterCoroutineSplit` to handle this. This    │
│ function is responsible for informing the CGSCC pass manager about the changes.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The assertion failure suggests that the call graph update logic is flawed. When `CoroSplitPass` runs on the SCC containing `foo` and `bar`, it modifies `foo`. The  │
│ original function `foo` is replaced by the ramp function, and new functions are created. The pass then tries to update the call graph.                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The key problem is that `CoroSplitPass` modifies a function within the current SCC (`foo`) and then tries to update the call graph in a way that makes the pass     │
│ manager believe the SCC itself has been invalidated.                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ Looking at `CoroSplit.cpp`, the function `updateCallGraphAfterCoroutineSplit` is where the call graph is updated. It removes outgoing edges from the original       │
│ function node, adds new nodes for the newly created functions, and then tries to have the pass manager re-analyze the modified and new functions.                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The assertion `!UR.InvalidatedSCCs.count(C)` suggests that the `CGSCCUpdateResult` `UR` is being marked with the current SCC `C` as invalidated. This can happen if │
│ a function within the SCC is deleted or if the SCC structure is broken in a way the pass manager can't handle during an SCC pass.                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ In this case, `foo` is not deleted, but it is heavily modified. The mutual recursion between `foo` and `bar` means they are in the same SCC. When `coro-split` runs │
│ on this SCC, it processes `foo`. The call from `bar` to `foo` remains (now to the ramp function), and the call from `foo` to `bar` is moved to a new resume         │
│ function. The new resume function is part of the same SCC as `bar` and the ramp function.                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ A similar issue was fixed in LLVM commit `d34a39a89b89`. The problem was that when a function in an SCC is modified, `updateCGAndAnalysisManagerForFunctionPass`    │
│ might incorrectly conclude that the SCC is invalidated if it can't find the function in the SCC's node list anymore. The fix was to re-scan the function's callees  │
│ to update the call graph *before* invalidating analyses, which gives the pass manager a consistent view.                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ In `CoroSplit.cpp`, `updateCallGraphAfterCoroutineSplit` calls `updateCGAndAnalysisManagerForFunctionPass` for the modified original function (`N.getFunction()`).  │
│ This seems to be the source of the problem. The function is modified in-place, and this update logic is likely what triggers the assertion.                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The fix from `d34a39a89b89` was to add `CG.rescanFunction(F)` before calling `updateCGAndAnalysisManagerForFunctionPass`. This ensures the call graph edges are     │
│ up-to-date before the analysis manager update logic is invoked.                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ Let's apply a similar fix. In `CoroSplit.cpp`, inside `updateCallGraphAfterCoroutineSplit`, before calling `updateCGAndAnalysisManagerForFunctionPass` for the      │
│ original function node `N`, I will add a call to `CG.rescanFunction(N.getFunction())`. This should update the call graph's view of the modified function's outgoing │
│ edges, preventing the pass manager from thinking the SCC has been invalidated.                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The relevant code snippet in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Coroutines/CoroSplit.cpp` is:                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                              │
│ // ... in updateCallGraphAfterCoroutineSplit ...                                                                                                                    │
│   // Recompute analyses for the original function, which is now the ramp                                                                                            │
│   // function.                                                                                                                                                      │
│   updateCGAndAnalysisManagerForFunctionPass(CG, SCC, N, AM, UR, FAM);                                                                                               │
│ // ...                                                                                                                                                              │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ I will change it to:                                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                              │
│ // ... in updateCallGraphAfterCoroutineSplit ...                                                                                                                    │
│   // Recompute analyses for the original function, which is now the ramp                                                                                            │
│   // function.                                                                                                                                                      │
│   CG.rescanFunction(N.getFunction());                                                                                                                               │
│   updateCGAndAnalysisManagerForFunctionPass(CG, SCC, N, AM, UR, FAM);                                                                                               │
│ // ...                                                                                                                                                              │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ This seems like the correct and minimal change to fix this specific crash, based on the symptoms and previous related fixes.                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                             │
│ sed -i '/updateCGAndAnalysisManagerForFunctionPass(CG, SCC, N, AM, UR, FAM);/i \ \ CG.rescanFunction(N.getFunction());'                                             │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Coroutines/CoroSplit.cpp                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                 │
